mindmap
  root((AI Drift & Failure))
    Drift Types
      Input Drift
        Feature distributions shift
        New regions or user segments
        Data collection changes
      Concept Drift
        Input-output relationships evolve
        Past patterns lose predictive power
        Gradual or sudden onset
      Label Drift
        Target definitions change
        Policy or regulatory reclassification
        Model optimizes for obsolete objective
    Detection Systems
      Statistical Monitoring
        Kolmogorov-Smirnov tests
        Population Stability Index
        Distribution comparison
      Confidence Tracking
        Prediction certainty drops
        Classification ratio shifts
        Out-of-distribution signals
      Human Signals
        Frontline anomaly reports
        User feedback channels
        Escalation to review
    Resilience Design
      Redundancy
        Backup models
        Ensemble approaches
        Rule-based overrides
      Recovery
        Rollback to last good version
        Canary deployments
        Staged rollouts
      Playbooks
        Incident checklists
        Escalation protocols
        Communication templates
    Governance
      Accountability
        Model pause authority
        Rollback ownership
        Board notification triggers
      Reporting
        Incident normalization
        Regulatory disclosure
        Retrospective sharing
      Culture
        Psychological safety
        Detection rewarded
        Failure drills practiced